FT  30 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Persona valued at Pounds 19.3 for placing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN CANE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Persona Group, a distributor of personal computer network and communications
products, is coming to the market through a placing at 160p a share, valuing
the company at Pounds 19.3m.
The placing is sponsored by Beeson Gregory. Some 8.4m shares are being
placed, 6.8m on behalf of existing shareholders and 1.6m on behalf of the
company. Some Pounds 1.98m is being raised for the company.
At the placing price the price earnings multiple is 14.4; the notional net
annual dividend is 3.84p and the notional gross dividend yield at the
placing price is three per cent.
