FT  30 MAR 94 / UK Company News: Morgan Grenfell Latin trust raises Pounds
64m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Morgan Grenfell has raised Pounds 64.2m with the launch of its Latin
American Companies investment trust, Pounds 53m of which came from an
institutional placing.
A similar fund, the Inca trust from Edinburgh Fund Managers, raised about
Pounds 30m during its placing. The result of its public offer is not yet
known.
Both trusts had initially set higher targets, but Morgan Grenfell said that
given market conditions during the offer period, it was very satisfied with
the amount raised. The placing for a third Latin American fund, from
Templeton, is still under way.
Dealings in the Morgan trust's shares and warrants are due to start
tomorrow.
