restoring the financial stability of the company,' said Mr Peter Prowting,
chairman. He is hoping to achieve 'a balance between rental income and
funding costs' in 1995, helped by new lettings and interest rate changes.
Losses per ordinary share were reduced to 21.1p against 126.7p.
