FT  30 MAR 94 / UK Company News: C&amp;W Russian purchase
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW ADONIS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Cable and Wireless, the telecommunications group, has spent Dollars 39.9m
(Pounds 27.3m) on a 25.1 per cent stake in Petersburg Long Distance, a
private telecommunications concern, which is building a network in Russia's
second city.
PLD has a 59 per cent stake in a joint venture with St Petersburg's
state-owned telecommunications operator.
The company is building a network to help plug unmet demand for local,
national and international telecoms services in the city, the directors
stated.
PLD also has a 50 per cent stake in a cellular mobile communications venture
in Kazakhstan.
