FT  30 MAR 94 / NZ offer to repay Nauru
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WELLINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
New Zealand said yesterday it would pay compensation to the Pacific island
state of Nauru for environmental damage caused by phosphate mining, Reuter
reports from Wellington. New Zealand, Australia and Britain jointly mined
for phosphate until Nauru won independence in 1968.
Mr Don McKinnon, foreign minister, said Wellington and London would each
contribute ADollars 12m (Dollars 8.5m) towards a total compensation package
of ADollars 107m.
