<HEADLINE>
FT  29 MAR 94 / International Company News: Armco to take Dollars 20m charge
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PITTSBURG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Armco, the US steel group, plans to close all its Empire-Detroit steel
division's facilities, laying off 1,300 workers and taking a Dollars 20m, 19
cents per share charge, against first-quarter earnings, Reuter reports from
Pittsburg.
The company said it expected the shutdown to last until mid-1995, when its
new thin-slab continuous caster is completed at Empire-Detroit's Mansfield,
Ohio, plant.
</TEXT>
