<TEXT>
Legal &amp; General, the life assurance company, has put the Millbank Tower,
adjacent to London's River Thames, up for sale at a price of Pounds 73m,
writes Vanessa Houlder.
The building's largest tenant is the government, together with Pearson,
British Gas, Vickers, Royal Bank of Scotland and Ferranti.
L&amp;G is selling the property to reduce its weighting of property in Victoria,
following a decision to invest Pounds 60m in refurbishing a government-let
building in Victoria Street.
The life assurance companies remain a net investor in property, having
exchanged contracts on about Pounds 200m of properties this year.
